\begin_layout Section
Confidence sets of infinite diameter
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Fix some measurable space 
\begin_inset Formula $(\Omega,\mathcal{F})$
\end_inset

, and let 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

 be a family of dominated probability measures defined on this measurable
 space, and 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{\Pi}$
\end_inset

 a partition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

.
 Recall that a partition of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

 is a collection of disjoint non-empty subsets of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

 such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\bigcup_{\pi\in\Pi}\pi=\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

.
 When 
\begin_inset Formula $P\in\mathcal{P}$
\end_inset

, we will use the standard notation 
\begin_inset Formula $[P]$
\end_inset

 to denote the unique 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

 containing 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

.
 We will also use the notation 
\begin_inset Formula $[p]$
\end_inset

 when 
\begin_inset Formula $p$
\end_inset

 is a density derived from 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Definition
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "def:confidence set"

\end_inset

 A 
\emph on
confidence set
\emph default
 of level 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 is a family of rejection sets 
\begin_inset Formula $\{R(\pi)\},\pi\in\Pi$
\end_inset

 such that
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\sup_{\pi\in\Pi}\sup_{P\in\pi}P(R(\pi))\leq\alpha.\label{eq:confidence set}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

If the inequality is an equality, the confidence set has 
\emph on
size
\emph default
 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This definition of confidence sets might look slightly unfamiliar, but it
 is a straight-forward generalization of the definitions in 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after "Definition 9.1.5"
key "Casella2002-lg"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after "Section 3.5"
key "lehmann2006testing"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 Usually, a confidence is defined as a set 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
